    }
    writer {
      name: "Alvin Sargent"
    }
    rating: "Decent"
    comments: "The dialogue is corny again as it is filled with many memeable lines (which also does make this movie iconic); the humor is unintentionally funny again because the movie reverted to being campy (enter Bully Maguire); the symbolism is there because the movie does tackle deep themes like arrogance, selfishness, and love, but not on a deeper level like the previous movie; the foreshadowing is pretty good"
  }
